	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Wow, its amazing the gossip that goes around on this little gnome. I on and off (when low on cash) camp her for a night or two and she isn't that hard to make pop, here (as with all random spawns, ie: ancient cyclops) is the trick.<BR>
<BR>
Head on over to the ruins by Surefall Glade entrance and park your butt at loc 4678.75,-806.69.<BR>
From here you can see the hills looking out South, Southwest.<BR>
Now at about 8pm EQ time, skeletons, decaying skeletons, and dread corpses will start walking down the and eventually sit (collapse into a pile) in 6 key locations around the ruins. Here are those locations:<BR>
<BR>
1. 4765.30, -831.89<BR>
2. 4646.57, -813.18 (down the hill a bit, keep an eye on this spot as it seems to be her favorite PH and is hard to see when the skele plops down).<BR>
3. 4631.25, -891.63<BR>
4. 4654.05, -1005.54<BR>
5. 4793.73, -963.38<BR>
6. Center of the ruins<BR>
<BR>
Now anyone of these is a placeholder for her and she can spawn from anyone of them, the PH (and her as well) DO NOT spawn at the above locations, this is just where they end up at. Most will come from down the hill or from blackburrow entrance. So if you have tracking like I do, you can nail her or the placeholders before they ever wind up at their despawn points.<BR>
Now you can just clear out the areas I stated above, or play it safe like I do and kill ANY undead thing you see in nuking radius around the ruins (mainly to clear my tracking list ;p).<BR>
Now if you lack tracking its a tad more difficult as kill stealers can intercept her before she gets to the ruins, but DO NOT run around looking for her, its important you kill all the potential placeholders or she can literally take weeks to spawn.<BR>
I have killed her probably close to 100 times in the year or so I have been playing and probably gotten the stone 10 times, it is kinda rare, but I have gotten 2 stones in 10 hours helping a friend, and zero in 2 days, as with all rare loots, its luck more then anything.<BR>
To dispel all the rumors, Tovax and Varsoon are NOT related to her spawning. Tovax is the common placeholder for the named gnoll Furgutt or whatever and also drops a note that will force Varsoon to spawn. Now rumors say that if you kill Varsoon, Pyzjn will spawn and resurrect him as Varsoon the Undying, and she uses the glowing black stone to do this (as it IDs as Varsoons Heart), I have never confirmed this, and since I have never once killed Varsoon and had her spawn I just dismiss the rumors and stick to the way I always been doing it.<BR>
Now, I never once posted this before because if the info got out, people would be farming the stone 24/7 the value would go down and I'd lose money, but now with Kunark out, the stones value has dropped as their are competive items out there and its not such a loss.<BR>
Anyways have fun, and use this info lightly, constant camping of her, and your stone will be about as valuable as serp bracers are (hmmm, went from 750 plat to 50 plat in price, think about it).
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
